-- Hostages Taken By Gunman In Ingolstadt Town Hall
-- B y   S t u a r t   M e t z l e r
-- 2013-08-19T09:31:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-19/hostages-taken-by-gunman-in-ingolstadt-town-hall.html
A gunman has taken an unknown number
of staff hostage at the Ingolstadt town hall in  Germany . German
news channel N24 has reported that the situation is unrelated to
today’s visit by Germany’s Chancellor Angela Merkel, who is due 
in Ingolstadt at around 5 p.m.  Guenther Beck, spokesman for the Ingolstadt police, told
Bloomberg on the telephone that the gunman entered the building
at about 9 a.m. The gunman is in contact with the police, but has
yet to issue any demands.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stuart Metzler at 
 smetzler4@bloomberg.net  